article.headline: N. Colorado 57, Idaho St. 37
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Elliott Lloyd scored 11 points and Northern Colorado dealt Idaho State its 19th consecutive road loss, winning 57-37 on Thursday night. Devon Beitzel added 10 points for Northern Colorado (9-7, 5-0 Big Sky). The Bears are off to their first 5-0 start in the Big Sky in their five years in the conference. Kenny McGowen had 12 points for Idaho State (5-11, 1-3). Leading scorer Broderick Gilchrest went scoreless and was held out of the second half with a sprained right ankle. The Bengals haven't won on the road since Nov. 28, 2009, and are 0-9 on the road this season.
